<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUN 94 / Commodities and Agriculture: Heavy rain washes out Thai
rubber output
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BANGKOK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Unusually heavy rainfall in southern Thailand has reduced June rubber output
by an estimated 50 per cent, according to senior officials of the state
Rubber Research Institute, reports Reuter from Bangkok.
In past years, rubber production in June was around 100,000 tonnes, but the
unusual weather pattern this year has cut that figure in half, creating
shortages and causing prices to surge.
