<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUN 94 / UK Company News: Restructure helps Allied Radio cut loss
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Allied Radio, which operates the licences for Radio Mercury and Mercury
Extra in the south-east, cut pre-tax losses from Pounds 901,000 to Pounds
364,000 in the six months to March 31.
Mr Brian Rowbotham, chairman, said the improvement followed the successful
capital restructuring, resolved at general meetings and now subject only to
formal approval of the Scottish court. An underwritten rights issue closed
in May with 46 per cent taken up.
An 11 per cent dip in turnover on continuing operations to Pounds 1.34m was
anticipated at the time of the restructuring which Mr Rowbotham said
reflected the new management's policy of restricting advertising minutage in
order to improve audience figures, while increasing spot yield rates to
advertisers.
This strategy had resulted, as budgeted, in revenue in the short term being
reduced until the full increase in rates began to take full effect, he
added.
The chairman said he was confident revenue would accelerate as higher yields
were obtained in a more buoyant market, and Allied's broad base of
advertisers responded to improved programming and promotion.
Losses per share before reconstruction were 0.8p (2.01p) or 0.3p after, on a
pro forma basis.
</TEXT>
