FT  29 JUN 94 / UK Company News: St James's Place
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir Mark Weinberg, joint chairman of St James's Place Capital, the financial
services group, received a 73 per cent pay rise last year, from Pounds
305,000 to Pounds 529,000. This followed a leap in group pre-tax profits
from Pounds 12.3m to Pounds 81.1m in the year ended March 31 1994.
Sir Mark's Pounds 224,000 increase accounted for almost one quarter of the
rise in the group's total wages and salaries bill, which increased by Pounds
1m to Pounds 4.7m. However, Lord Rothschild, the other joint chairman, took
a pay cut from Pounds 311,000 to Pounds 297,000. Excluding the joint
chairmen, emoluments of the highest paid director moved up from the Pounds
305,001 to Pounds 310,000 range to between Pounds 330,001 and Pounds
335,000.
