<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUN 94 / UK Company News: C&amp;W in partnership talks with Belarus
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Cable and Wireless, the telecommunications group, has signed a deal with the
government of Belarus giving it exclusive negotiating rights for nine months
to become a strategic partner in the privatisation of the state
telecommunications company of the former Soviet republic.
If successful, the deal could lead to C&amp;W taking a large minority stake in
the state company, in return for upgrading Belarus's antiquated telecoms
network.
C&amp;W has significant interests in the Baltic region, including minority
stakes in the Latvian state telecommunications company and in Tele2, the
main competitor to the Swedish state telecommunications operator.
