FT  29 JUN 94 / UK Company News: Alfred McAlpine rights 76% taken up
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Alfred McAlpine has received 9.52m acceptances for its 12.6m rights issue at
205p per share, representing a 75.7 per cent take-up.
Subscribers have been procured for the remaining 3.05m shares for which
acceptances were not received, at a premium of 0.1p per share.
The company announced the issue on June 2 with a call for Pounds 25m to
finance land purchases.
The shares fell 1p to 206p on the news.
