<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUN 94 / UK Company News: Sutcliffe Speakman Pounds 1.1m back in
black
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sutcliffe Speakman continued its recovery in the second half and for the
full year to end-March swung from losses of Pounds 6.56m to profits of
Pounds 1.1m pre-tax.
All arrears of preference dividends will be paid on July 28 and ordinary
dividends are resumed via a proposed 0.5p payment.
Earnings per share emerged at 1.51p compared with previous losses of 19.02p.
Turnover of continuing activities improved from Pounds 21.5m to Pounds
22.6m. The Lancashire-based group is engaged in activated carbon technology
and environmental protection systems. There was a further Pounds 839,000
(Pounds 7.72m) from discontinued activities.
Mr Frank Buckley, chairman, said the progress made marks the end of a
transitional stage in the group's recovery. He will stand down as chairman
at the annual meeting in July and be succeeded by Mr Earnest Tyerman, a
non-executive member of the board since 1991.
Mr Buckley said the balance sheet at end-March showed a significant change
brought about by the rights issue and related refinancing agreements in July
1993.
