<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUN 94 / Arts: Washington Opera appoints Domingo
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Placido Domingo has been appointed as the new artistic director of
Washington Opera. Announcing the decision at a press conference yesterday,
he said he planned to continue singing and conducting in the major opera
houses of the world but at the same time maintain 'full control of all
musical and artistic matters,' in Washington. He also plans to perform in
one Washington production each year.
In 14 years under the outgoing director Martin Feinstein, Washington Opera
has grown from an interesting provincial company with a Dollars 2m annual
budget to one of international stature with an Dollars 11.5m, selling more
than 100,000 tickets each year. Mobil Corporation has agreed to sponsor the
opera house for the next three years.
