FT  29 JUN 94 / Royal Ordnance contract extended
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The government has extended part of a big ammunition contract awarded to
Royal Ordnance last year in a deal worth about Pounds 40m to the British
Aerospace subsidiary.
Mr Jonathan Aitken, defence procurement minister, announced last night that
the government had agreed to extend the small arms element of the Pounds
200m contract for a further two years to cover 1998-99 and 1999-2000.
He said the decision should help to maintain jobs at the factory at Radway
Green in Cheshire, which employs nearly 600 people.
The company won the original five-year contract to supply ammunition ranging
from small arms to tank shells last October against stiff competition. BAe
is considering collaboration between Giat, the French state-owned arms
manufacturer, and Royal Ordnance.
