<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUN 94 / Industry warned on foreign rivals
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A research centre to help industries close performance gaps with foreign
companies was launched yesterday by Cardiff Business School.
Professor Daniel Jones, director, warned that most UK companies must at
least double productivity and sharply improve quality if they are to survive
against competition, particularly from from south-east Asia.
The centre and partners Andersen Consulting have embarked on a benchmarking
exercise between 75 UK and Japanese companies following a similar exercise
which compared the UK and Japanese motor components industries. That found
Japanese companies on average to be twice as productive as UK counterparts,
and 100 times better on quality.
