FT  29 JUN 94 / Oxford colleges change names
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Two Oxford University colleges yesterday voted to change their names in
honour of prominent benefactors. Manchester College, which does not yet have
full collegiate status within the university, is to be The Manchester
Academy and Harris College, in recognition of support from Sir Philip
Harris, former chairman of Harris Queensway.
Rewley House, which caters for mature and part-time students, becomes
Kellogg College in recognition of donations from the WK Kellogg Foundation,
a US charitable body.
