FT  29 JUN 94 / Union challenge to water company
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Unison, the public services and utilities union, yesterday said it was
launching an action in the High Court challenging South West Water's refusal
to recognise the union. The company withdrew recognition for its 1,200
Unison members in October.
Unison is seeking to apply the recent European Courts of Justice ruling
which held the UK government had been in breach of its obligations under the
Acquired Rights Directive.
Unison said the action was the first time a union had attempted to apply
European law on union recognition to a former nationalised industry.
