<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUN 94 / World Cup '94: Brazil and Sweden through - Salenko sets goal
record
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Romario scored a stunning, solo equalising goal at the Silverdome in Detroit
to ensure Brazil finished top of Group B last night after a 1-1 draw with
second-place Sweden.
Kennet Andersson's 24th-minute goal was the first the Brazilians had
conceded in the tournament but both teams comfortably qualified for the
second round.
In the other Group B game, Oleg Salenko scored a record five goals as Russia
crushed Cameroon 6-1 in San Francisco to give them a chance of going through
as a third-place finisher.
Salenko struck in the 16th, 41st, 45th, 73rd and 75th minutes - all five
goals with his right foot - making him the first player to score five goals
in one game at the World Cup finals. The previous best, shared by nine
players, was four goals: most recently by Spain's Emilio Butragueno against
Denmark in the 1986 finals.
Dmitri Radchenko added Russia's sixth in the 82nd minute.
Even a goal by 42-year-old Roger Milla with his first touch as a second-half
substitute was not enough to inspire Cameroon's Lions, who finished bottom
on one point and were eliminated.
</TEXT>
