for Paramount Communications, the film and publishing group, and was seen as
a way for BellSouth to get a toehold in the entertainment business. At the
time of the agreement, QVC's stock was trading at over Dollars 50 but it has
been below Dollars 40 since April.
Mr Diller said QVC could be expected to seek expansion opportunities beyond
electronic retailing, including possibly into production of fiction and
non-fiction programming.
Speaking later, he said the company's basic television shopping service had
restored double-digit sales growth after a five-month slowdown.
